<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04EED42BA8EFE529DAF27F0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04EED42BA8EFE529DAF27F0" blockId="5.[226,1361,401,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) is derived from the name of the mountain range (Banan) where the 
<typeStatus id="548C883BC04EED42B8CEFE769CB927F0" box="[674,729,437,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04EED41BA8EFE219FEC248B" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="253" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04EED42BA8EFE219C312465" blockId="5.[226,1361,482,580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04EED42B8C8FE219D6927DF" box="[676,777,482,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04EED42BE67FE219A1027DF" box="[1035,1136,482,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head blackish; pronotum dark-brown; elytra castaneous; abdomen dark-brown; legs castaneous; antennae dark-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04EED42BA8EFD969D6A2562" blockId="5.[226,1362,597,835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Head (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04EED42BB54FD969FE52450" box="[312,389,597,625]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) 1.12 times as long as broad and of oval shape (i.e., lateral margins convex in dorsal view); posterior angles smoothly convex, practically obsolete; punctation relatively fine and moderately dense; interstices with fine and shallow microreticulation, mostly approximately as broad as diameter of punctures, partly narrower; median dorsal portion between eyes with sparsely punctate patch. Eyes relatively small, approximately 1/4 as long as distance from posterior margin of eye to posterior constriction in dorsal view. Antenna approximately 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04EED42B80EFCE49CA12562" box="[610,705,807,835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04EED42BA8EFC969DCB25FE" blockId="5.[226,1361,853,991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04EED42BB1FFC969FA12550" box="[371,449,853,881]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.3 times as long as broad and 0.97 times as broad as head; punctation slightly coarser than that of pronotum and moderately dense; interstices with extremely shallow, almost obsolete microreticulation, on average slightly broader than diameter of punctures; midline broadly impunctate.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF486611C04EED42BA8EF8569F5C21EB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518393" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6518393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518393/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" startId="5.[226,283,1941,1966]" targetBox="[226,1359,1001,1916]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04EED42BA8EF8569F5C21EB" blockId="5.[226,1361,1941,1994]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04EED42BA8EF8569F58218F" bold="true" box="[226,312,1941,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Map 1</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus id="548C883BC04EED42BB23F8569FE9218F" box="[335,393,1941,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Type</typeStatus>
localities of 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04EED42B85FF8569DC0218C" authority="KOCH" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1944" box="[563,928,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharense">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04EED42B85FF8569D2C218F" box="[563,844,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Lathrobium bucharense</emphasis>
KOCH
</taxonomicName>
(triangle) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04EED42BE0CF8569A90218F" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[1120,1264,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bananum" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04EED42BE0CF8569A90218F" box="[1120,1264,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">L. bananum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27057F0C04EED42BE93F8569B31218F" box="[1279,1361,1941,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(circle).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04DED41BA8EFEC19CCE2763" blockId="6.[226,1361,258,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04DED41BB25FEC19FFD273F" box="[329,413,258,286]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) 0.86 times as long as pronotum; punctation shallow and ill-defined. Length of hind wings not examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04DED41BA8EFE969AC327B4" blockId="6.[226,1361,341,405]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">Abdomen approximately as broad as elytra; punctation dense and fine; interstices with distinct microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883699C04DED41BA8EFE649DF7245A" blockId="6.[226,1361,423,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">
♂: sternites III-VI unmodified; sternite VII slightly depressed in posterior median portion, posterior margin weakly concave in the middle; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04DED41BE28FE0E9AF027C8" box="[1092,1168,461,489]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, with shallow median impression in posterior half, this impression with two longitudinal clusters of numerous modified, stout black setae, posterior margin broadly and weakly concave; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04DED41B825FDF89CD62476" box="[585,694,571,599]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">Figs 6-7</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CCF9B7CC04DED41B8A6FDF89D4B2476" box="[714,811,571,599]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
long, ventral process with distinct median keel basally and with long and slender ventral process.
