<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04DED41BA8EFD7E9ACB254A" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04DED41BA8EFD7E9ACB254A" blockId="6.[226,1361,701,875]" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">
Comparative notes: In external and the male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04DED41BED5FD7E9B3124F8" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[1209,1361,701,729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bananum">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04DED41BED5FD7E9B3124F8" box="[1209,1361,701,729]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">L. bananum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04DED41BBBCFD229CE624DC" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1944" box="[464,646,737,765]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharense">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04DED41BBBCFD229CE624DC" box="[464,646,737,765]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">L. bucharense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, most likely its adelphotaxon, but distinguished by the darker coloration of the elytra, legs, palpi, and antennae, and by the shape of the ventral process of the aedeagus (median carina of different shape; ventral process shorter in relation to aedeagal capsule). For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04DED41B923FC8C9A63254A" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1944" box="[847,1027,847,875]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharense">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04DED41B923FC8C9A63254A" box="[847,1027,847,875]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">L. bucharense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC04DED41BE57FC8C9ACB254A" box="[1083,1195,847,875]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="253">Figs 1-3.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
